wiki.summary: On June 1st, 2018, this song was leaked online through YouTube and SoundCloud. Supposedly this song was made sometime after Castles II, a collaborative project released February 7, 2017, between GBC members Lil Peep and fellow rapper and best friend, Tracy. On June 14th, 2018, the song was released for streaming through Apple Music, Spotify, and Tidal. However, it was deleted hours shortly after its initial release because it was supposedly released unauthorized on those services. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: On June 1st, 2018, this song was leaked online through YouTube and SoundCloud. Supposedly this song was made sometime after Castles II, a collaborative project released February 7, 2017, between GBC members Lil Peep and fellow rapper and best friend, Tracy. On June 14th, 2018, the song was released for streaming through Apple Music, Spotify, and Tidal. However, it was deleted hours shortly after its initial release because it was supposedly released unauthorized on those services. Finally, on November 9, 2018, it was released on the album Come Over When You’re Sober, Pt. 2. This version being remastered and completed. Read more on Last.fm.
